00:06:19.147 --> 00:06:20.980
DAVID MOLK: So I thought
to organize my talk

00:06:20.980 --> 00:06:25.950
in three categories, first, the
disadvantages and the drawbacks

00:06:25.950 --> 00:06:29.125
of lack of compassion, the
problems that arise when there

00:06:29.125 --> 00:06:34.480
is a lack of love and compassion
between people, secondly,

00:06:34.480 --> 00:06:37.920
the great advantages
and benefits of love

00:06:37.920 --> 00:06:43.030
and compassion, and thirdly,
how love and compassion

00:06:43.030 --> 00:06:44.010
can develop.

00:06:46.950 --> 00:06:49.041
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:06:55.020 --> 00:06:56.603
DAVID MOLK: First
of all, the benefits

00:06:56.603 --> 00:06:58.960
of love and compassion,
they're so important.

00:07:02.051 --> 00:07:03.800
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:07:27.120 --> 00:07:29.890
DAVID MOLK: So myself,
being a Buddhist,

00:07:29.890 --> 00:07:33.580
to say a word about it
in a Buddhist context,

00:07:33.580 --> 00:07:36.180
in all the ways of
Buddhism, all the vehicles,

00:07:36.180 --> 00:07:38.700
whether it's the
Theravadan or bodhisattvan

00:07:38.700 --> 00:07:43.090
vehicle or the Tantric
practice, love and compassion

00:07:43.090 --> 00:07:46.610
is really the basis
of the foundation

00:07:46.610 --> 00:07:50.190
of all of Buddhist teachings.

00:07:50.190 --> 00:07:53.310
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:07:58.682 --> 00:08:00.140
DAVID MOLK: So
something that is so

00:08:00.140 --> 00:08:03.420
important in the context
of Buddhist teachings

00:08:03.420 --> 00:08:07.520
is also extremely important
for the world at large.

00:08:07.520 --> 00:08:09.630
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:08:39.820 --> 00:08:42.809
DAVID MOLK: So a lot of
people may have the impression

00:08:42.809 --> 00:08:46.160
that compassion is something
you feel for others.

00:08:46.160 --> 00:08:48.300
It's other-focused.

00:08:48.300 --> 00:08:50.850
It's something that's
for their benefit,

00:08:50.850 --> 00:08:54.570
not understanding that it's very
beneficial for the person who

00:08:54.570 --> 00:08:57.566
develops that
compassion themselves.

00:08:57.566 --> 00:09:00.288
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:09:01.174 --> 00:09:02.590
DAVID MOLK: So
it's not like that.

00:09:02.590 --> 00:09:06.491
It's not just for
the sake of another.

00:09:06.491 --> 00:09:08.240
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:09:24.170 --> 00:09:27.695
DAVID MOLK: Because when
someone genuinely develops

00:09:27.695 --> 00:09:31.990
love and compassion
in a very sincere way,

00:09:31.990 --> 00:09:35.540
that actually brings great
happiness to that person

00:09:35.540 --> 00:09:37.470
himself.

00:09:37.470 --> 00:09:39.466
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:10:07.066 --> 00:10:08.590
DAVID MOLK: So the
problem is, when

00:10:08.590 --> 00:10:10.786
there's a lack of
love and compassion,

00:10:10.786 --> 00:10:15.210
is that a person becomes
too self-centered, too

00:10:15.210 --> 00:10:17.022
self-focused.

00:10:17.022 --> 00:10:19.970
They're unable to look outwards.

00:10:19.970 --> 00:10:24.030
It's as if this closes the
door on their awareness

00:10:24.030 --> 00:10:28.602
to outer world and
other living beings.

00:10:28.602 --> 00:10:31.130
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:10:37.310 --> 00:10:39.900
DAVID MOLK: So it's good
open, to widen our horizons,

00:10:39.900 --> 00:10:44.570
to think in a more vast way.

00:10:44.570 --> 00:10:46.360
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:11:21.550 --> 00:11:27.530
DAVID MOLK: So when we
undergo great difficulties,

00:11:27.530 --> 00:11:32.650
painful situations, and so
on, then from the Buddhist

00:11:32.650 --> 00:11:35.210
view-- in the
context of Buddhism,

00:11:35.210 --> 00:11:38.440
we see that as something
that we've created ourselves

00:11:38.440 --> 00:11:39.380
in terms of karma.

00:11:39.380 --> 00:11:44.000
We've planted the
seeds for that.

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:47.576
But if we just remain focused on
our problem and our suffering,

00:11:47.576 --> 00:11:50.956
we get angry about it,
get self-pitying about it,

00:11:50.956 --> 00:11:53.090
then OK, we've got one problem.

00:11:53.090 --> 00:11:56.047
But our mental attitude
is piling another problem

00:11:56.047 --> 00:11:59.176
on top of that.

00:11:59.176 --> 00:12:01.720
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:12:14.298 --> 00:12:17.670
DAVID MOLK: So we may
experience the same kinds

00:12:17.670 --> 00:12:19.480
of sufferings and difficulties.

00:12:19.480 --> 00:12:22.250
But to me, the big difference
is in the way that we handle

00:12:22.250 --> 00:12:24.230
and the way that we
deal with it, especially

00:12:24.230 --> 00:12:29.390
if we a more vast, open
minded kind of perspective.

00:12:29.390 --> 00:12:31.710
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:13:11.840 --> 00:13:16.310
DAVID MOLK: So when someone
is practicing Buddhism,

00:13:16.310 --> 00:13:18.840
there are different levels
at which it can be practiced.

00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:21.915
And at the level of
the highest capacity,

00:13:21.915 --> 00:13:24.130
the person remains
very much focused

00:13:24.130 --> 00:13:32.950
on attainment of enlightenment
in a very short time

00:13:32.950 --> 00:13:34.580
or a short number of lifetimes.

00:13:38.800 --> 00:13:40.550
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:13:49.066 --> 00:13:50.690
DAVID MOLK: Now the
power of their mind

00:13:50.690 --> 00:13:54.580
is really able to provide
happiness for them continually,

00:13:54.580 --> 00:13:58.695
both in this lifetime and into
the future lifetimes as well.

00:13:58.695 --> 00:14:00.445
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:14:00.445 --> 00:14:02.550
DAVID MOLK: So this
is the first level

00:14:02.550 --> 00:14:05.300
in which that power of
the practice or the mind

00:14:05.300 --> 00:14:08.470
enables a person to
maintain happiness

00:14:08.470 --> 00:14:10.401
in this and all lifetimes.

00:14:10.401 --> 00:14:12.150
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:14:47.259 --> 00:14:48.800
DAVID MOLK: So at
that highest level,

00:14:48.800 --> 00:14:53.321
those problems never create
a problem or unhappiness

00:14:53.321 --> 00:14:54.195
for the practitioner.

00:14:54.195 --> 00:14:58.650
But at a minimum
level, then there's

00:14:58.650 --> 00:15:00.750
these special way
in which the person

00:15:00.750 --> 00:15:04.490
is able to deal with problems is
that they have a lot of tools,

00:15:04.490 --> 00:15:08.540
a lot of methods from the
teachings, which enables them

00:15:08.540 --> 00:15:13.455
to transform what would be
difficult circumstances,

00:15:13.455 --> 00:15:17.080
bad conditions of various
types, into something that's

00:15:17.080 --> 00:15:20.010
beneficial for their
spiritual path,

00:15:20.010 --> 00:15:24.410
to transform negative conditions
into positive conditions

00:15:24.410 --> 00:15:25.595
for their spiritual path.

00:15:25.595 --> 00:15:27.345
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:15:28.410 --> 00:15:30.910
DAVID MOLK: He said, the dharma
provides them with the tools

00:15:30.910 --> 00:15:31.930
to do that.

00:15:31.930 --> 00:15:35.380
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
Just like in food, OK,

00:15:35.380 --> 00:15:39.780
food-- when you get
hungry, you have to eat.

00:15:39.780 --> 00:15:41.110
Dharma is just like food.

00:15:44.580 --> 00:15:45.810
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:16:38.490 --> 00:16:40.995
DAVID MOLK: And
at the very least,

00:16:40.995 --> 00:16:44.340
the dharma should
provide a person

00:16:44.340 --> 00:16:49.476
with means of dealing with
difficulties and problems

00:16:49.476 --> 00:16:51.350
