bodhisattvas such
as His Holiness

00:22:44.910 --> 00:22:46.790
the Dalai Lama
living in this world

00:22:46.790 --> 00:22:51.440
today, the fact that he can
remain in a happy state of mind

00:22:51.440 --> 00:22:57.650
and provide so much
and happiness to others

00:22:57.650 --> 00:23:00.320
is a result of
this being focused

00:23:00.320 --> 00:23:06.470
on the welfare of others, having
given up self-centeredness

00:23:06.470 --> 00:23:08.400
and selfishness.

00:23:08.400 --> 00:23:11.841
Because of this
altruistic mind, he

00:23:11.841 --> 00:23:14.610
remains in a state of happiness
and able to bring so much

00:23:14.610 --> 00:23:17.180
happiness to others.

00:23:17.180 --> 00:23:18.930
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:23:52.502 --> 00:23:53.960
DAVID MOLK: But as
for the opposite

00:23:53.960 --> 00:23:57.245
of that, which we see
so much this world today

00:23:57.245 --> 00:24:00.780
in our own experience
and in other worse

00:24:00.780 --> 00:24:03.770
realms of existence,
all those sufferings

00:24:03.770 --> 00:24:07.790
that arise come from this
self-centered attitude,

00:24:07.790 --> 00:24:14.020
the selfish attitude, which
then causes people to look down

00:24:14.020 --> 00:24:19.540
on others and disparage
others, and then on that basis

00:24:19.540 --> 00:24:21.160
create negative karma.

00:24:21.160 --> 00:24:25.320
And it causes so much suffering.

00:24:25.320 --> 00:24:27.480
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:24:57.090 --> 00:24:59.740
DAVID MOLK: And in the
world in general and here,

00:24:59.740 --> 00:25:04.180
no matter what
situation you look at,

00:25:04.180 --> 00:25:08.690
happiness can't really be
sustained by ones self alone.

00:25:08.690 --> 00:25:11.460
We're all interconnected.

00:25:11.460 --> 00:25:15.150
And the only way that the
welfare of any one person

00:25:15.150 --> 00:25:20.005
can arise is in
dependence upon others.

00:25:20.005 --> 00:25:22.305
So especially in
this world today

00:25:22.305 --> 00:25:24.570
in which we're so
interconnected,

00:25:24.570 --> 00:25:26.690
all of their happiness
depends on others.

00:25:26.690 --> 00:25:31.277
It's as if we've
become big family.

00:25:31.277 --> 00:25:33.026
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:26:33.750 --> 00:26:36.236
DAVID MOLK: So to take
the example of a merchant

00:26:36.236 --> 00:26:37.861
or someone who's
selling things or even

00:26:37.861 --> 00:26:44.710
to take the example
of Google, in order--

00:26:44.710 --> 00:26:46.410
it's not possible
for just a few people

00:26:46.410 --> 00:26:48.910
to create this
completely on their own.

00:26:48.910 --> 00:26:51.660
There needs to be people
who want that service, who

00:26:51.660 --> 00:26:53.410
want those goods.

00:26:53.410 --> 00:26:55.954
And in the case of
Google, there are

00:26:55.954 --> 00:26:59.141
millions of people who
use and look at it.

00:26:59.141 --> 00:27:05.750
And that then brings benefit
to the works and people

00:27:05.750 --> 00:27:07.270
involved with Google as well.

00:27:07.270 --> 00:27:13.750
So there's a great benefit
for ones self and others.

00:27:13.750 --> 00:27:14.904
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:27:14.904 --> 00:27:16.654
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:27:27.600 --> 00:27:29.140
DAVID MOLK: And
to think about it

00:27:29.140 --> 00:27:34.490
in a vaster sense of the world
that all of our happiness

00:27:34.490 --> 00:27:38.380
depends upon others.

00:27:42.110 --> 00:27:45.012
So yes, there is effort that
we need to put forth ourselves,

00:27:45.012 --> 00:27:47.642
maybe a good percentage of it.

00:27:47.642 --> 00:27:49.350
But if it was just
all left to ourselves,

00:27:49.350 --> 00:27:51.110
we wouldn't be
able to manage it.

00:27:51.110 --> 00:27:56.480
The success depends upon others.

00:27:56.480 --> 00:27:59.000
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:28:11.920 --> 00:28:14.250
DAVID MOLK: So how can these
qualities be developed?

00:28:14.250 --> 00:28:18.490
How can we go about developing
love and compassion?

00:28:18.490 --> 00:28:21.190
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:28:39.800 --> 00:28:41.994
DAVID MOLK: So there
are two ways in Buddhism

00:28:41.994 --> 00:28:43.330
for this development.

00:28:43.330 --> 00:28:46.690
And I'm going to focus
on one of them, which

00:28:46.690 --> 00:28:50.090
uses the example of
oneself to understand

00:28:50.090 --> 00:28:52.480
others and understand
that just as oneself

00:28:52.480 --> 00:28:56.240
doesn't want to experience
suffering, so it is for others.

00:28:56.240 --> 00:29:00.960
Just as oneself would like
to experience happiness,

00:29:00.960 --> 00:29:04.885
understand it's just
the same for others.

00:29:04.885 --> 00:29:06.635
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:29:13.010 --> 00:29:17.235
DAVID MOLK: So in our own case,
we're completely sure, 100%,

00:29:17.235 --> 00:29:19.199
that we don't want
problems, suffering.

00:29:19.199 --> 00:29:23.127
We want happiness
and fulfillment.

00:29:23.127 --> 00:29:26.060
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:29:29.726 --> 00:29:32.340
DAVID MOLK: So the fact is
that every living creature

00:29:32.340 --> 00:29:36.098
has exactly that same attitude.

00:29:36.098 --> 00:29:39.050
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:30:07.025 --> 00:30:10.055
DAVID MOLK: So the first
step is to open our mind

00:30:10.055 --> 00:30:13.430
to this kind of understanding
that that is true,

00:30:13.430 --> 00:30:16.330
that just as I want happiness
and don't want suffering,

00:30:16.330 --> 00:30:21.370
that is completely true for
another and for all others.

00:30:21.370 --> 00:30:23.552
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:30:54.360 --> 00:30:58.720
DAVID MOLK: So that in itself
can prevent a lot of problems.

00:30:58.720 --> 00:31:03.260
When we get an urge to
strike out at someone else

00:31:03.260 --> 00:31:06.910
or to hurt another,
there's no other means

00:31:06.910 --> 00:31:09.840
necessary like meditation
or recitation of a mantra,

00:31:09.840 --> 00:31:11.615
but just simply to
bring that thought

00:31:11.615 --> 00:31:14.640
to mind that, oh, this person
doesn't want suffering.

00:31:14.640 --> 00:31:18.640
This person wants happiness
just as much as I do.

00:31:18.640 --> 00:31:23.690
And that very awareness, it can
bring a stop to that impulse

00:31:23.690 --> 00:31:26.880
to strike out and harm another.

00:31:26.880 --> 00:31:29.280
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:32:10.530 --> 00:32:15.120
DAVID MOLK: So then by
contemplating that continually

00:32:15.120 --> 00:32:17.520
and thinking both
about the benefits that

00:32:17.520 --> 00:32:22.456
derive from warm, harmonious,
compassionate mind attitude

00:32:22.456 --> 00:32:27.070
towards others as
well as the drawbacks

00:32:27.070 --> 00:32:29.970
and the great problems
that arise from maintaining

00:32:29.970 --> 00:32:34.560
a selfish,
self-centered attitude,

00:32:34.560 --> 00:32:41.186
continually contemplating the
pros and cons of that, then

00:32:41.186 --> 00:32:48.420
along with that, then
bring it into whereas

00:32:48.420 --> 00:32:52.640
how it relates to
others, and realizing

00:32:52.640 --> 00:32:55.006
that they don't want suffering.

00:32:55.006 --> 00:32:58.986
And they have these same kinds
of problems and dynamics.

00:32:58.986 --> 00:33:03.366
And so to bring that into the
way that one relates to others,

00:33:03.366 --> 00:33:06.910
you'll be more kind to.

00:33:06.910 --> 00:33:08.660
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:33:46.030 --> 00:33:49.990
DAVID MOLK: So the work
that we do is not easy.

00:33:49.990 --> 00:33:53.150
And also this development
of love and compassion

00:33:53.150 --> 00:33:55.340
is not something
that's very easy to do.

00:33:55.340 --> 00:33:59.660
So it takes continual
perseverance and patience.

00:33:59.660 --> 00:34:04.080
There needs to be a lot
of patience, forbearance

00:34:04.080 --> 00:34:09.006
for developing these attitudes
and working with others.

00:34:09.006 --> 00:34:12.213
So patience really
need to be there as

00:34:12.213 --> 00:34:17.834
like a foundation or a great
aid to the development of love

00:34:17.834 --> 00:34:19.340
and compassion.

00:34:19.340 --> 00:34:21.695
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:34:28.500 --> 00:34:31.429
DAVID MOLK: So it's
like the container that

00:34:31.429 --> 00:34:34.840
needs to be there to hold,
or the enclosure there

00:34:34.840 --> 00:34:37.790
that needs to be there in
order to support that love

00:34:37.790 --> 00:34:39.878
and compassion.

00:34:39.878 --> 00:34:42.352
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:35:12.360 --> 00:35:18.050
DAVID MOLK: So in the context
of the vows of a bodhisattva,

00:35:18.050 --> 00:35:20.675
there's a very
strong determination

00:35:20.675 --> 00:35:24.530
that I'm not going to do
anything to harm others.

00:35:24.530 --> 00:35:28.720
And if at all possible,
I'm going to help them.

00:35:28.720 --> 00:35:29.870
I'm going to benefit them.

00:35:29.870 --> 00:35:33.650
So there needs to be this kind
of determination and patience

00:35:33.650 --> 00:35:37.850
that's behind maintaining,
developing this attitude.

00:35:37.850 --> 00:35:39.600
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:35:40.696 --> 00:35:42.550
DAVID MOLK: So
patience, forbearance

00:35:42.550 --> 00:35:44.940
is something
extremely important.

00:35:44.940 --> 00:35:48.440
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:36:22.456 --> 00:36:23.830
DAVID MOLK: So
patience can apply

00:36:23.830 --> 00:36:28.450
in a lot of different areas,
patience towards an enemy,

00:36:28.450 --> 00:36:34.590
patience towards dharma and
spiritual development, patience

00:36:34.590 --> 00:36:37.010
in the work that
you're doing to serve

00:36:37.010 --> 00:36:39.890
others, which is not easy.

00:36:39.890 --> 00:36:44.890
It takes a lot of patience
to do that hard work

00:36:44.890 --> 00:36:47.940
for the benefit of others.

00:36:47.940 --> 00:36:51.710
So that's a very
valid form of patience

00:36:51.710 --> 00:36:54.330
and valuable form of patience.

00:36:54.330 --> 00:37:00.125
There can be patience for
people that annoy you,

00:37:00.125 --> 00:37:04.620
that make you angry, and so on.

00:37:04.620 --> 00:37:07.440
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:37:15.960 --> 00:37:18.680
DAVID MOLK: So it's said
in the teachings of Buddha

00:37:18.680 --> 00:37:22.510
that patience is the
greatest of austerities.

00:37:22.510 --> 00:37:25.480
It's one of the most
difficult practices,

00:37:25.480 --> 00:37:32.270
one of the most difficult
practices to maintain.

00:37:32.270 --> 00:37:38.015
So it's a great austerity to
be able to practice patience.

00:37:38.015 --> 00:37:40.370
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:38:02.135 --> 00:38:04.780
DAVID MOLK: He said, without
anybody to annoy you,

00:38:04.780 --> 00:38:06.860
then who are you going
to be patient with?

00:38:06.860 --> 00:38:08.440
[LAUGHTER]

00:38:08.440 --> 00:38:11.532
You know, if everyone's just
fine and having a great time,

00:38:11.532 --> 00:38:14.310
then how am I going to persevere
in developing this love

00:38:14.310 --> 00:38:14.945
and compassion?

00:38:14.945 --> 00:38:19.020
What kind of challenges
is that going to present?

00:38:19.020 --> 00:38:20.891
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:38:36.504 --> 00:38:37.920
DAVID MOLK: So
love and compassion

00:38:37.920 --> 00:38:39.640
is something that
needs to be developed

00:38:39.640 --> 00:38:42.296
in place of hatred and anger.

00:38:42.296 --> 00:38:46.620
So it needs to displace those.

00:38:46.620 --> 00:38:49.470
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:39:00.780 --> 00:39:02.480
DAVID MOLK: And so
in that case, then

00:39:02.480 --> 00:39:05.490
we need to be able to develop
love and compassion for someone

00:39:05.490 --> 00:39:10.190
who is an adversary, someone
who provokes that anger

00:39:10.190 --> 00:39:11.641
and hatred in us.

00:39:11.641 --> 00:39:13.390
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:39:42.040 --> 00:39:45.460
DAVID MOLK: Then so--
[SPEAKING TIBETAN].

00:39:45.460 --> 00:39:48.050
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN] He forget.

00:39:48.050 --> 00:39:50.300
[LAUGHTER]

00:39:56.606 --> 00:39:57.772
DAVID MOLK: Simple to learn.

00:40:01.252 --> 00:40:04.855
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE: He needs
to hear, as he [INAUDIBLE].

00:40:04.855 --> 00:40:05.829
Anyway--

00:40:05.829 --> 00:40:07.780
[LAUGHTER]

00:40:07.780 --> 00:40:09.850
DAVID MOLK: [SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:13.750
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:40:24.400 --> 00:40:26.540
DAVID MOLK: So to support
that development of love

00:40:26.540 --> 00:40:31.685
and compassion, there definitely
needs to be this patience

00:40:31.685 --> 00:40:37.970
and perseverance to develop it-

00:40:37.970 --> 00:40:39.720
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:40:39.720 --> 00:40:40.821
DAVID MOLK: --from
starting right

00:40:40.821 --> 00:40:42.585
in with those around
you, your family

00:40:42.585 --> 00:40:45.710
and your close associates.

00:40:45.710 --> 00:40:49.140
So not getting angry with
enemies-- and that also

00:40:49.140 --> 00:40:52.833
needs to start right at home to
keep that patience and loving

00:40:52.833 --> 00:40:56.920
attitude right towards the
relations in one own family.

00:40:56.920 --> 00:40:59.405
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:41:25.389 --> 00:41:26.180
DAVID MOLK: Think--

00:41:26.180 --> 00:41:28.641
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE: Think--

00:41:28.641 --> 00:41:29.557
DAVID MOLK: Globally--

00:41:29.557 --> 00:41:31.832
KHENPO KARTEN
RINPOCHE: --globally.

00:41:31.832 --> 00:41:32.540
DAVID MOLK: Act--

00:41:32.540 --> 00:41:34.264
KHENPO KARTEN
RINPOCHE: Act locally.

00:41:34.264 --> 00:41:35.980
[LAUGHTER]

00:41:38.145 --> 00:41:40.456
DAVID MOLK: So he really
likes this phrase,

00:41:40.456 --> 00:41:43.230
think globally, act locally.

00:41:43.230 --> 00:41:45.756
We want to keep our
intentions very, very vast.

00:41:45.756 --> 00:41:47.270
That's what we're intending.

00:41:47.270 --> 00:41:50.380
But where to start with it
is right in our own vicinity

00:41:50.380 --> 00:41:53.621
and our own family as well.

00:41:53.621 --> 00:41:55.370
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:42:07.980 --> 00:42:10.330
DAVID MOLK: So we need to
develop this within ourselves

00:42:10.330 --> 00:42:12.280
first.

00:42:12.280 --> 00:42:15.705
And then from there, it can
spread out through the world.

00:42:15.705 --> 00:42:17.455
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:42:48.120 --> 00:42:51.600
DAVID MOLK: So this needs to
be practiced in the family

00:42:51.600 --> 00:42:52.230
to begin with.

00:42:52.230 --> 00:42:56.340
And if there is love and caring
between parents and members

00:42:56.340 --> 00:42:59.000
of a family, then it can
spread to the neighbors.

00:42:59.000 --> 00:43:00.825
It can spread to the vicinity.

00:43:00.825 --> 00:43:03.970
It can spread to the country.

00:43:03.970 --> 00:43:05.580
And this is really
they only way.

00:43:05.580 --> 00:43:08.590
Because lacking inner
peace ourselves,

00:43:08.590 --> 00:43:11.390
if we want to try to provide
inner peace for the world,

00:43:11.390 --> 00:43:13.402
there's no way that's
going to happen.

00:43:19.570 --> 00:43:22.010
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:43:45.930 --> 00:43:47.440
DAVID MOLK: Now
when we trace back

00:43:47.440 --> 00:43:49.821
the root cause of all
the different conflicts

00:43:49.821 --> 00:43:52.775
and sufferings that
exist in the world,

00:43:52.775 --> 00:43:55.085
they really do trace
back to this lack

00:43:55.085 --> 00:43:59.962
of caring between people, lack
of love, lack of compassion.

00:43:59.962 --> 00:44:03.364
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:44:29.320 --> 00:44:32.800
DAVID MOLK: So there needs
to be this kind of attitude

00:44:32.800 --> 00:44:36.520
to alleviate problems in the
world, in our own country,

00:44:36.520 --> 00:44:40.270
and around the world--
this understanding

00:44:40.270 --> 00:44:45.316
that others have exactly
the same wish for happiness

00:44:45.316 --> 00:44:50.310
and wish to avoid suffering and
be free of problems as I do,

00:44:50.310 --> 00:44:54.910
and I'm going to do my
very best to help them.

00:44:54.910 --> 00:44:56.570
And even if I can't,
then at least,

00:44:56.570 --> 00:44:59.310
I'm not going to harm them.

00:44:59.310 --> 00:45:03.566
And keep this kind of
determination and commitment.

00:45:03.566 --> 00:45:05.560
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:45:23.600 --> 00:45:27.343
DAVID MOLK: And so if peace
is going to come in the world,

00:45:27.343 --> 00:45:29.690
it will need to
come in this way.

00:45:29.690 --> 00:45:31.370
It can't come from outside.

00:45:31.370 --> 00:45:35.190
It has to be developed
within ourselves.

00:45:35.190 --> 00:45:36.940
And when it is developed
within ourselves,

00:45:36.940 --> 00:45:38.720
then there's the
real possibility

00:45:38.720 --> 00:45:40.490
that it can spread to the world.

00:45:40.490 --> 00:45:45.670
And if we do this, some
time in the future,

00:45:45.670 --> 00:45:49.510
there will actually
be peace on earth.

00:45:49.510 --> 00:45:51.260
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:46:20.470 --> 00:46:24.490
DAVID MOLK: So in the practice
of the teachings of Buddha,

00:46:24.490 --> 00:46:26.810
we develop a
feeling of closeness

00:46:26.810 --> 00:46:30.850
and warmth towards others just
as if they were our closest

00:46:30.850 --> 00:46:33.920
relations such as our mother.

00:46:33.920 --> 00:46:37.896
And even in recitations,
we'll refer to all living

00:46:37.896 --> 00:46:40.140
beings as our mother.

00:46:40.140 --> 00:46:42.650
In other words, in Tibetan,
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]--

00:46:42.650 --> 00:46:47.545
all sentient beings are my
mother, who have been mother.

00:46:47.545 --> 00:46:52.330
And so even if we don't
contemplate that deeply,

00:46:52.330 --> 00:46:54.880
to just say the
words, to me, they're

00:46:54.880 --> 00:46:59.320
very powerful words to bring
in that sense of that closest

00:46:59.320 --> 00:47:04.611
relationship with other living
beings, no matter who they are.

00:47:04.611 --> 00:47:06.360
KHENPO KARTEN RINPOCHE:
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:47:41.850 --> 00:47:45.980
DAVID MOLK: So it's so
obvious, all the problems

